tspan.tspan: The ongoing growth of compute power and data processing capabilities of supercomputers
high performance systems, previously driven by Moore's law and now by the
processing capabilities of GPUs, TPUs, and AI accelerators.
MCTS samples multiple tree searches to some depth and propagates final values up
the path, which keeps statistics for each (state, action)-pair (edge). At the end, it
chooses the most promising action from the root and prepares the next move.
